<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6679&amp;p=64844#p64844"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I think it's really neat that you can accomplish simple affine transformations just by using Offsets Per Tile mode, combined with X scrolling. I never would have thought that this would work so well.<br /></div><br />It works so well because cos(x) is close to 1 if x is close to 0, and because sin(x) is close to x if x is close to 0. (1st degree taylor devlopment).<br /><br />I always had the feeling the "offset per tile" mode on the SNES went seriously under-used. Chrono Trigger's title screen, Contra III's first boss, and the elevators in Super Double Dragon's stage 1, it's all I can remember.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Jul 25, 2010 5:28 am</p><hr />
